Closes https://github.com/apache/kylin/pull/2072

## Proposed changes

Dev design doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wUNd8U1u-w8T-qQUReplPhDFkETj3AtFr_Shex501ls/edit?usp=sharing


- add config and checker to enable or disable the cube planner1 when build a new segment or refresh a segment. 
- add property of `@JsonProperty("layout_cost_based_pruned_list")` which is used to indicate whether the rulebaseindex has been recommended by the cost based algorithm.
- insert a  new stage of `COST_BASED_PLANNER` in `CUBING` job, and the new stage is used to create task to collect the statistics and run the cost based algorithm.
- use the `biginteger` instead of `long` to represent the cuboio
- migrate the algorithm from kylin3.1 to kylin5.0 without major changes, and just make some adaptive changes. For example, change the cubeio from `long` to `biginteger`
- migrate the IT/UT for the recommended algorithm from kylin3.1 to kylin5.0

issue_title: KYLIN-5748 Skip build flat table for index build job if all new created indexes can be built from existed parent index
body:
For an index build job, if all the new added indexes can be built from their existed parent index. No index was built from new created flat table.
For this case, there won't be any data inconsistency across indexes. And there is no need to build a new flat table to serve the stage of index build by layer.
So I think we can skip stage BUILD DICT and stage GENERATE FLAT TABLE for an index build job in condition that all new added indexes can be built from their existed parent index

issue_title: KYLIN-5545 Try best to interrupt running queries and limit the number of queries to run.
body:
## Proposed changes

1. Add a new property `kylin.query.pushdown-concurrent-running-threshold=10` to control the concurrency of the queries pushed down, 10 running queries by default, which will be bond to a Semaphore instance in JVM scope.

2. The pushed down query will calling `Semaphore` instance's `tryAcquire(long timeout, TimeUnit unit)` to acquire the chance to run, so the waiting queries could be interrupted if failed in `330s` by default.

## Why these changes?
1. `QueryLimiter` won't working then the server is not in `downgrade` state, which means no limitations on the number of queries pushed down to run, therefore we need another strategy to accomplish the goal.
2. During retrieving the file status, it gives us a chance to react to the interruption, so as to terminate the planning queries.

This is IT for cube planner:
1. basic test case
2. corner test case: delete one dimension after building one segment

partition and no-partition have different logic and different construct for the `AdaptiveSpanningTree` and `SegmentFlatTableDesc`, they are hard to be combined together.

On the original codebase, the code for partition and no-partition are separated, such as `PartitionMaterializedFactTableView` and `MaterializedFactTableView`.

If you want to combine the logic for partition and no-partition, we can do this in the next follow-up PR.
But I find the logics in the `build`, `merge` and other `job` are all  divided into partition and non-partition

I am not an expert for scala, so it's better for me to implement it using java.
We can create an issue to track the enhancement.

From the cuboio, we can only get the combination of the columnid.
In order to make consistent with the order of `sortOfDims`, we need to sort the them by `sortOfDims`

For exampleÔºö
`sortOfDims`:  column3, column1,column4,column6,column7.
`cubeoid`: 0000 1001, from the cuboid, we can only know the `colOrder` contain the column7 and column4, and can't get the order for them.

we don't need to specify that which index is the result of the cube planner. 
The cube planner is used for pruning the layouts generated by the `RuleBasedIndex`
